    h1 The sassiest way to play with Sass, Compass, &amp; LibSass

    p
      | SassMeister is a playground for 
      a(href='http://sass-lang.com') Sass
      | , 
      a(href='http://compass-style.org/') Compass
      | , and 
      a(href='http://sass-lang.com/libsass') LibSass
      | . Add some Sass and SassMeister will show you the rendered CSS. SassMeister supports both 
      a(href='http://thesassway.com/articles/sass-vs-scss-which-syntax-is-better') Sass and SCSS syntaxes
      | , all 
      a(href='http://sass-lang.com/docs/yardoc/file.SASS_REFERENCE.html#output_style') output styles
      | , and an ever-expanding list of Sass libraries.

    h2 Current extensions

    ol
      //- Per http://www.alexkras.com/11-tips-to-improve-angularjs-performance/
      //- `::` is one-time binding
      li(ng-repeat='(name, extension) in extensions')
        a(href='{{extension.homepage}}') {{::name}}

    p
      i
        | Not all extensions are available on all compilers. For instance, SassyJSON requires features that are only available in Sass 3.3.

